<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="10" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Usually large and densely pilose, body shape never arched; antennal flagellum elongate cylindrical to paddle-shaped, sometimes tapered but never stylate, usually lacking terminal setae; postpronotal lobes never meeting medially; wing venation complete to wing margin (rarely reduced), cells m3, d, bm and basal r4+5 typically present, closed distally; tibial spines present (rarely absent); larvae exclusively parasitoids of mygalomorph spiders.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
